---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Two-Letter Words — Essential Scrabble Word Guides"
  description="Master every two-letter word in Scrabble. Complete lists, high-scoring picks, rare words, and memorization techniques. Free guides, no signup."
  keywords="two letter scrabble words, 2 letter words scrabble, two letter words list, scrabble two letter words with q, scrabble two letter words with z, free scrabble word list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many two-letter words are valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are 127 valid two-letter words in the Official Scrabble Players Dictionary (OSPD/TWL) used in North American tournaments. The international dictionary (SOWPODS/Collins) has even more." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why are two-letter words so important in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Two-letter words let you play parallel to existing words, scoring points from multiple words in a single turn. They also help you use difficult letters like Q, X, and Z, and allow plays in tight board positions where longer words won't fit." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring two-letter word in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ZA (an informal word for pizza) scores 11 points at face value — Z is worth 10 and A is worth 1. QI also scores 11 points (Q=10, I=1). Both become much higher on premium squares." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 flex items-center gap-1">
      <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
      <span class="mx-1">›</span>
      <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Two-Letter Words</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-8">
      Two-letter words are the secret weapon of every strong Scrabble player. These 10 guides cover the 
      complete list, the highest-scoring picks, tricky letters like Q, X, and Z, memorization techniques, 
      and printable references you can study anywhere. Learn them all and watch your scores climb.
    </p>

    <!-- Post grid -->
    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <a href="/blog/two-letter-scrabble-words-complete-list/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Complete List of Two-Letter Scrabble Words</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Every valid two-letter word in one place — the definitive reference for tournament and casual players.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/best-two-letter-words-scrabble/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Two-Letter Words in Scrabble</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The highest-value and most versatile two-letter words ranked by strategic impact on your game.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-with-q/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words With Q</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">QI is your lifeline — learn how to play the Q without a U and turn a tough tile into easy points.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-with-x/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words With X</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">AX, EX, XI, XU — the four ways to play X in two letters and maximize its 8-point value.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-with-z/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words With Z</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">ZA, ZO, and more — deploy the 10-point Z tile quickly with these essential two-letter plays.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/most-useful-two-letter-words/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Most Useful Two-Letter Words</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The 20 two-letter words you'll use most often — ranked by frequency and strategic versatility.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/memorizing-two-letter-words/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">How to Memorize Two-Letter Words</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Proven techniques — grouping, mnemonics, spaced repetition, and practice drills that actually work.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/rare-two-letter-scrabble-words/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Rare Two-Letter Words</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The obscure two-letter words most players don't know — surprise your opponents with unexpected plays.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-with-j/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words With J</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">JO is the only two-letter J word — learn when and how to deploy the 8-point tile in tight spots.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-with-k/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words With K</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">KA, KI, and more — the 5-point K tile deployed in quick two-letter plays for reliable scoring.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-with-v/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words With V</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Every valid two-letter V word — clear the awkward 4-point V tile without wasting a turn.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-complete-strategy/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Complete Two-Letter Word Strategy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Advanced tactics for two-letter plays — parallel scoring, hooks, defensive blocks, and endgame combos.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/two-letter-words-by-alphabet/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words by Starting Letter</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Organized A to Z — quickly find every two-letter word that starts with the letter you're holding.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/printable-two-letter-word-list/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Printable Two-Letter Word List</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">A clean, printer-friendly reference card you can study offline or keep beside the board.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/is-aa-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is AA a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! AA is valid — it's a type of volcanic lava. Learn when and how to play it for maximum points.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/is-jo-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is JO a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! JO is the only two-letter word with J — essential for deploying this 8-point tile quickly.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/is-ox-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OX a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! OX scores 9 points at face value — discover the best plays and hooks using OX.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/is-xi-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is XI a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! XI scores 9 points — the Greek letter that's a lifesaver for playing X in tight spots.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/is-xu-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is XU a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! XU is a Vietnamese monetary unit — another way to use X in two letters for 9 points.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-qi-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is QI a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! QI is valid in both SOWPODS and TWL — the highest-scoring two-letter word at 11 points.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-za-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ZA a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Yes! ZA is valid — South African slang for pizza. A must-know two-letter Z word worth 11 points.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-ze-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ZE a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">ZE is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL — a gender-neutral pronoun added to Collins Scrabble Words.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-ew-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EW a Scrabble Word?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">EW is valid in TWL (added 2014) but NOT in SOWPODS — an exclamation of disgust worth 5 points.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-li-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is LI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">LI is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's a Chinese unit of distance (~500 metres). Learn LI strategy for rack-clearing plays.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-na-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is NA a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">NA is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL (North American). It scores 2 points and means 'no' in Scottish dialect. Check which dictionary your game uses before playing NA.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-nu-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is NU a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">NU is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the 13th letter of the Greek alphabet. Compare NU with other Greek letter words in Scrabble.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-po-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is PO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">PO is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a chamber pot (archaic). Learn PO strategy, scoring potential, and unusual 2-letter words.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-sh-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is SH a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">SH is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL (North American). It scores 5 points and is an interjection meaning 'quiet'. A vowelless word — learn when you can play it.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/is-ti-a-scrabble-word/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is TI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">TI is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's a plant (Cordyline) or musical note (do-re-mi-fa-sol-la-TI-do). Learn TI strategy.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Links to other category pages -->
    <div class="mt-12 border-t border-gray-800 pt-8">
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">More Categories</h3>
      <div class="grid gap-3">
        <a href="/blog/word-validity/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
